         <abstract>
            <p>A new algorithm is presented for the best L&lt;sub&gt;p&lt;/sub&gt; approximation of a continuous function over a discrete set or a finite interval with &lt;latex&gt;$2 &lt; p &lt; \infty$&lt;/latex&gt;. Methods to accelerate the convergence of the Rice-Usow extension of Lawson's algorithm as well as the new algorithm are presented, and the result of a numerical example is given.</p>
          </abstract>
